LEGEND["<div style='width:320px;text-align:left'><b style='font-size:15px'>LAYER LEGEND</b><br/><span style='font-size:12px'>🟣 layer 0 — the flow (time)<br/>🔵 layer 1 — the core (signed)<br/>🟢 layer 2 — the projection (moduli)<br/>🟠 layer 3 — physics (observables)<br/>🟪 Part II — the second tier (binding, P6)<br/>🟦 Part III — structure growth (fσ₈)<br/>⬜ gray dashed — invariant checks<br/>🟥 red dashed — the core's boundary</span></div>"]

ACT["<div style='width:300px;text-align:center'><b style='font-size:19px'>𝒮[φ] = ∫ ½ φ̇² dt</b><br/><span style='font-size:12px'>the action of the free flow φ; varying it gives φ̈ = 0 — nothing accelerates the flow</span></div>"]
PHI["<div style='width:280px;text-align:center'><b style='font-size:19px'>φ = ω·t</b><br/><span style='font-size:12px'>the phase grows uniformly at rate ω — irreversible time itself, the model's only dynamics</span></div>"]

S["<div style='width:280px;text-align:center'><b style='font-size:19px'>S = R·sin(φ/2)</b><br/><span style='font-size:12px'>the scale of space (signed); an odd function of φ, it passes through zero and changes sign</span></div>"]
O["<div style='width:280px;text-align:center'><b style='font-size:19px'>O = R·cos(φ/2)</b><br/><span style='font-size:12px'>the scale of objectness (signed); shifted by ¼ turn relative to S</span></div>"]
NORM["<div style='width:300px;text-align:center'><b style='font-size:19px'>S² + O² = R²</b><br/><span style='font-size:12px'>the master law: the norm is constant (a circle); scale only flows between the poles</span></div>"]
W["<div style='width:300px;text-align:center'><b style='font-size:17px'>W = S·O′ − O·S′ = −R²/2</b><br/><span style='font-size:12px'>the constant Wronskian: one pole at zero — the other at its maximum (quadrature)</span></div>"]
SIG["<div style='width:300px;text-align:center'><b style='font-size:16px'>σ = sign(S), sign(O)<br/>O_full = O · σ_S</b><br/><span style='font-size:12px'>the sign phase; objectness inherits the sign of space at the Mush crossing</span></div>"]

PROJ["<div style='width:300px;text-align:center'><b style='font-size:17px'>π : O(φ) ↦ |O(φ)|</b><br/><span style='font-size:12px'>the modulus operation: the sign is cut off, the mirror branch is unobservable in principle</span></div>"]
P["<div style='width:290px;text-align:center'><b style='font-size:18px'>P = |S| = R·√(1−μ²)</b><br/><span style='font-size:12px'>observable space (≥0); light propagates along this pole</span></div>"]
Q["<div style='width:280px;text-align:center'><b style='font-size:18px'>Q = |O| = R·μ</b><br/><span style='font-size:12px'>observable objectness (≥0); the observer, their ruler and clock are made of it</span></div>"]
MU["<div style='width:290px;text-align:center'><b style='font-size:18px'>μ = |cos(φ/2)| = Q/R</b><br/><span style='font-size:12px'>the observable phase ∈ [0,1] — the fraction of objectness; the master variable of all the physics</span></div>"]
PQ["<div style='width:280px;text-align:center'><b style='font-size:18px'>P² + Q² = R²</b><br/><span style='font-size:12px'>the same norm in the projection: the modulus preserves the circle (a layer check)</span></div>"]

LT["<div style='width:320px;text-align:center'><b style='font-size:15px'>L(μ) ∝ μ ;  dτ = dt/μ ;  c = const</b><br/><span style='font-size:12px'>the observer's scales: the ruler stretches with objectness, the clock inversely to it; c = const pins both</span></div>"]
B["<div style='width:300px;text-align:center'><b style='font-size:19px'>b(μ) = √(1−μ²) / μ²</b><br/><span style='font-size:12px'>the scale factor — the heart of the model; all observable physics is derived from it</span></div>"]
Z["<div style='width:290px;text-align:center'><b style='font-size:17px'>1 + z = b(μ₀) / b(μ_e)</b><br/><span style='font-size:12px'>redshift — the ratio of the scale today to the scale at the moment of emission</span></div>"]
H["<div style='width:290px;text-align:center'><b style='font-size:17px'>|H_τ| = (2−μ²) / (1−μ²)</b><br/><span style='font-size:12px'>the expansion rate (units of k): at the Mush → ∞, at the bounce → 2</span></div>"]
Q3["<div style='width:320px;text-align:center'><b style='font-size:16px'>q = (−μ⁴+6μ²−4)/(μ⁴−4μ²+4)</b><br/><span style='font-size:12px'>the deceleration parameter; changes sign at z_t≈0.77 — acceleration from geometry, no dark energy</span></div>"]
RS["<div style='width:330px;text-align:center'><b style='font-size:13px'>r = (μ⁶−16μ⁴+20μ²−8)/(μ⁶−6μ⁴+12μ²−8)<br/>s = (r−1) / [3(q−½)]</b><br/><span style='font-size:12px'>the statefinder; at μ₀=0.76: r≈0.55, s≈0.16 — a departure from the ΛCDM point (r=1, s=0)</span></div>"]
CHI["<div style='width:340px;text-align:center'><b style='font-size:14px'>χ = (c/k)·[√(1−μ₀²)/μ₀²]·[√(1−μ₀²) − √(1−μ_e²)]</b><br/><span style='font-size:12px'>the comoving distance in closed form; the particle horizon is finite by itself</span></div>"]
DL["<div style='width:330px;text-align:center'><b style='font-size:15px'>d_L = (1+z)·χ ;  DM = 5·log₁₀(d_L/10pc)</b><br/><span style='font-size:12px'>the luminosity distance and the distance modulus — this is what is compared with the supernovae</span></div>"]
OM["<div style='width:320px;text-align:center'><b style='font-size:15px'>Om(z) = (E²−1)/((1+z)³−1)</b><br/><span style='font-size:12px'>a diagnostic, E = H/H₀; flat in ΛCDM, decreasing in DSIC — a falsifiable signature</span></div>"]

FIT["<div style='width:340px;text-align:center'><b style='font-size:15px'>CONFRONTATION WITH DATA</b><br/><span style='font-size:12px'>Pantheon+SH0ES (1657 SNe, anchor + covariance): Δχ² = +0.05 vs ΛCDM, χ²/dof = 0.878, H₀ ≈ 73, μ₀ = 0.76 — indistinguishable from ΛCDM. + DESI BAO, chronometers, age, z_t — all at a single μ₀ ≈ 0.76</span></div>"]
CMBN["<div style='width:320px;text-align:center'><b style='font-size:14px'>THE CORE'S BOUNDARY: the relic radiation (CMB)</b><br/><span style='font-size:12px'>at z=1090: 10936 vs 13873 Mpc, a 21% shortfall — the limit of the CORE (Part I); a consequence of the finite particle horizon (it saturates by z≈10). The second tier (below) closes this shortfall</span></div>"]

P6["<div style='width:320px;text-align:center'><b style='font-size:15px'>POSTULATE P6 — binding / detachment</b><br/><span style='font-size:12px'>the new entity of the second tier: until the monolith of objectness has parted, light has no path. The form of the correction is fixed by principle (amplitude A≡1, a sharp threshold)</span></div>"]
CORR["<div style='width:330px;text-align:center'><b style='font-size:15px'>correction ∝ 1/P = 1/√(1−μ²)</b><br/><span style='font-size:12px'>the addition to the path in the stuck-together phase of the medium; the integral = arcsin μ. Identically zero at μ ≤ μ_d (the late Universe is untouched)</span></div>"]
MUD["<div style='width:330px;text-align:center'><b style='font-size:16px'>μ_d = 0.9806  (z_detach ≈ 4.53)</b><br/><span style='font-size:12px'>the detachment threshold — a measured constant of the second tier; calibrated against ONE observation (the angle θ*), zero degrees of freedom</span></div>"]
DMC["<div style='width:340px;text-align:center'><b style='font-size:13px'>D_M corr = D_M + (c/k)·[arcsin μ_cmb − arcsin μ_d]</b><br/><span style='font-size:12px'>the corrected distance to the CMB = 13873 Mpc; 100·θ_model = 1.04110 (Planck: 1.04110) — exact closure</span></div>"]

GROW["<div style='width:340px;text-align:center'><b style='font-size:13px'>δ″ + (2 + dlnH/dlna)·δ′ − 1½·Ω_m(a)·δ = 0</b><br/><span style='font-size:12px'>linear perturbation growth on the DSIC background (GR limit); f = dlnδ/dlna. Status — a survival test, not a derivation from the core</span></div>"]
FS8["<div style='width:330px;text-align:center'><b style='font-size:15px'>fσ₈(z) = f·σ₈·δ(z)/δ(0)</b><br/><span style='font-size:12px'>checked against Gold-2017 (18 points): χ²/dof ≈ 0.7 — no worse than ΛCDM. The data are degenerate → the invariant S8 = 0.761 ± 0.013</span></div>"]

